  "texts": [
    "In fact, for possibility frames there is also a more liberal notion of selective subframe.",
    "(Compare this to the definition of cofinal subframes in Chagrov andZakharyaschev 1997, p. 295 andBezhanishvili 2006, p. 61.)",
    "Definition 5.52 (Subframes).",
    "Given a possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩, a subframe of F is a tupleF ′ = ⟨S ′, ⊑ ′, {R ′ i } i∈I, P ′ ⟩ such that: 1.",
    "S ′ ⊆ S; ⊑ ′ = ⊑ ∩ (S ′ × S ′), and R ′ i = R i ∩ (S ′ × S ′); 2."
  ],
